1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 20.1-03 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to nonresident upland and small game licenses; and to amend and
3 reenact section 20.1-03-07 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to nonresident hunting
4 licenses.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 20.1-03 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
7 and enacted as follows:
8 Nonresident upland and small game license.
9 Except as provided in section 20.1 - 08 - 04.9, a nonresident may purchase a nonresiden t
10 upland and small game license to hunt upland and small game, excluding waterfowl, during the
11 entire upland and small game hunting seasons. The governor, in the governor's proclamation,
12 may specify the number of licenses that may be issued and the manner in which licenses are to
13 be issued.
14 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 20.1-03-07 of the North Dakota Century Code is
15 amended and reenacted as follows:
16 20.1-03-07. Licenses to hunt, trap, or fish required of nonresidents.
17 1. Nonresidents, except as provided in sections 20.1-02-05, 20.1-03-07.3, and
18 20.1-03-08, may not:
19 1. a. Hunt, catch, take, or kill any small game without a nonresident small game
20 license. The nonresident small game license entitles the nonresident to hunt
21 small game for any period of fourteen consecutive days or any two periods of
22 seven consecutive days each. The hunting period for which the license is valid
23 must be designated on the license. A nonresident small game license is not
24 required to hunt waterfowl under section 20.1-03-07.1 or wild turkeys under
